ADDITIONAL TERMS — AuthServer

1. ATTRIBUTION
   If you use AuthServer as a base, template, or reference for your own
   authentication system, a credit to the original author (Prince Thawani)
   is appreciated but not required.

2. SECURITY RESPONSIBILITY
   This software is provided as a reusable authentication server. You are
   solely responsible for securing your own deployment, including but not
   limited to:
     - Changing default admin credentials before going to production
     - Keeping JWT secrets, database passwords, and SMTP credentials private
     - Keeping dependencies up to date
     - Configuring HTTPS in production environments
   The author accepts no liability for security breaches resulting from
   misconfiguration or misuse of this software.

3. CREDENTIAL PROTECTION
   Any secrets, credentials, or sensitive configuration values belonging to
   Prince Thawani (including but not limited to SMTP passwords, JWT secrets,
   and database credentials) that may appear in example files or documentation
   are illustrative only and must NOT be reused in any deployment.

4. NO WARRANTY FOR PRODUCTION USE
   While AuthServer is built with security best practices, it is provided
   without warranty of any kind. It is your responsibility to review,
   audit, and test the code before deploying it in a production environment
   handling real user data.

5. DERIVATIVE WORKS
   You are free to fork, modify, and build upon AuthServer for both personal
   and commercial projects. If you redistribute a modified version publicly,
   you must clearly state that changes were made to the original work and
   retain this license and copyright notice.

